{
  "text": "ihnát et al oligometastases are being explored (such as chemoembolization, thermal ablation, radiotherapy). [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Stereotactic body radiotherapy (SBRT) presents an emerging new technology that has shown high efficacy in ablating tumors at various disease sites. SBRT allows for the delivery of high-dose radiation in few fractions to the tumor with extreme accuracy, while minimizing the damage to normal surrounding tissue. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] The CyberKnife ® system (Accuray Incorporated, Sunnyvale, CA, USA) is an imageguided robotic system that delivers SBRT, tracks tumors during respiration, and automatically adjusts treatment for any patient movement. [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] The aim of the present paper is to offer an up-to-date review of current available data on the rationale, feasibility, safety, and outcomes of SBRT using the CyberKnife system in the treatment of patients with liver metastases.",
  "correct_citation": {
